This paper involves the application of deep reinforcement learning for decision-making in autonomous driving, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a simulator to evaluate the proposed method suggests that it may also fall under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning techniques for decision-making also suggests that it may fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of computer vision techniques for state representation may suggest that it falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the use of rule-based constraints for trajectory modification suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
